This paper deals with pricing queries over a database, which is a topic closely related to databases and information theory. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) and cs.IT (Information Theory) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the properties of pricing functions, which can be seen as a game-theoretic problem, leading to the possibility of cs.GT (Game Theory) being a relevant sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the avoidance of arbitrage, which is a security concern, leading to the possibility of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) being a relevant sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the computation of pricing functions, which can be seen as an algorithmic problem, leading to the possibility of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) being a relevant sub-category.
